verses.text_plain: Lord, I cry unto thee: make haste unto me; give ear unto my voice, when I cry unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 1Lord, I cry unto thee: make haste unto me; give ear unto my voice, when I cry unto thee.

verses.text_plain: Let my prayer be set forth before thee as incense; and the lifting up of my hands as the evening sacrifice.
verses.verse_html:
2Let my prayer be set forth before thee as incense; and the lifting up of my hands as the evening sacrifice. ▼
▼ set…: Heb. directed

verses.text_plain: Set a watch, O Lord, before my mouth; keep the door of my lips.
verses.verse_html: 3Set a watch, O Lord, before my mouth; keep the door of my lips.

verses.text_plain: Incline not my heart to any evil thing, to practise wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their dainties.
verses.verse_html: 4Incline not my heart to any evil thing, to practise wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their dainties.

verses.text_plain: Let the righteous smite me; it shall be a kindness: and let him reprove me; it shall be an excellent oil, which shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also shall be in their calamities.
verses.verse_html:
5Let the righteous smite me; it shall be a kindness: and let him reprove me; it shall be an excellent oil, which shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also shall be in their calamities. ▼
▼ me; it shall be a…: or, me kindly, and reprove me; let not their precious oil break, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ me; it shall be a…: or, me kindly, and reprove me; let not their precious oil break, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ me; it shall be a…: or, me kindly, and reprove me; let not their precious oil break, etc

verses.text_plain: When their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words; for they are sweet.
verses.verse_html: 6When their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words; for they are sweet.

verses.text_plain: Our bones are scattered at the grave’s mouth, as when one cutteth and cleaveth wood upon the earth.
verses.verse_html: 7Our bones are scattered at the grave’s mouth, as when one cutteth and cleaveth wood upon the earth.

verses.text_plain: But mine eyes are unto thee, O God the Lord: in thee is my trust; leave not my soul destitute.
verses.verse_html:
8But mine eyes are unto thee, O God the Lord: in thee is my trust; leave not my soul destitute. ▼
▼ leave…: Heb. make not my soul bare

footnotes.body_text: ▼ leave…: Heb. make not my soul bare
footnotes.body_html: ▼ leave…: Heb. make not my soul bare

verses.text_plain: Keep me from the snares which they have laid for me, and the gins of the workers of iniquity.
verses.verse_html: 9Keep me from the snares which they have laid for me, and the gins of the workers of iniquity.

verses.text_plain: Let the wicked fall into their own nets, whilst that I withal escape.
verses.verse_html:
10Let the wicked fall into their own nets, whilst that I withal escape. ▼
▼ escape: Heb. pass over

footnotes.body_html: ▼ escape: Heb. pass over
